          matchIssueKeys: ['gov_waste', 'audit_spending', 'gov_transparency', 'national_debt', 'cut_spending'],
          note: 'Stance chips read on the reform axis (nearly everyone favors "value for money"): “Supports” = pushes aggressive contracting oversight, competition and audits; “Mixed” = stewards or defends spending programs while backing efficiency, so the record cuts both ways. Positions come from each official’s documented record on a related spending, oversight or appropriations issue; the Stance Library has the full spread.',
